Installation

	Installation of CLE is straightforward, simply use the Eclipse Update Manager

	[[1]] From the Eclipse menu choose <<Help>>|<<Software Updates>>
	
	[[1]] Switch to the <<Available Software>> tab if needed
	
	[[1]] Press <<Add Site>>
	
	[[1]] Fill-in the dialog box with CLE update location: <<${project.url}/update>>

[s.gif]

[update-1.gif]

[s.gif]

	[[1]] In the Update window, you will now see the <<CUP/LEX>> category; select it then press <<Install>>.

[s.gif]

[update-2.gif]

[s.gif]

	[[1]] Confirm the installation by pressing <<Finish>>.

[s.gif]

[update-3.gif]

[s.gif]

	[[1]] Wait for the Update Manager to finish the plugin installation.
	
	[[1]] Press <<Yes>> to restart Eclipse.

[s.gif]

[update-4.gif]

[s.gif]

	[[1]] That's all!
